My poor, poor darling.

255
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:57,440
They only do these things
because they resent you.

256
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:00,240
Envy and spite...

257
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:03,040
that's all it is.

258
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,440
You watch, Ma.

259
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,280
I'm gonna be somebody in this town.

260
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,520
I always knew this.

261
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:21,560
The victim was asphyxiated,
likely with ether or chloroform.

262
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,440
Look under the scalp.

263
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,080
Humor me.

264
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,240
At the base of the skull,

265
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:33,360
there'd be an incision
about an inch long, sewn closed.

266
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,600
Wait a minute.

267
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,240
Yes.

268
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,760
How did I miss that?

269
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:42,720
An incision stitched closed
near the occipital.

270
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,920
Over a foreign object.

271
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,960
- What is it?
- It's a penny.

272
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,200
He's right.

273
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,960
- A penny?
- I know Milkie's MO.

274
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,880
No one could know that detail.

275
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,000
It isn't a copycat.

276
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:07,960
It can't be.

277
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:12,960
Ten years ago Randall Milkie
took an 1813 Liberty penny

278
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,440
just like this one,

279
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:16,800
and sewed it into the heads
of each of his victims.

280
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:17,880
Why?

281
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,520
How the hell do I know?

282
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,800
He bum-rushed me
wearing animal horns.

283
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,680
I shot him.
We didn't talk coin collecting.

284
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,760
You're sure no one else
could have found this out?

285
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,640
Milkie was the definition of a loner.

286
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,120
He didn't tell anybody.

287
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,040
We left it out of the file
intentionally.

288
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:33,240
- Suppressed evidence.
- We Easter-egged it.

289
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:36,960
We figured a killer like the Goat had
a good chance of drawing admirers.

290
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,440
Yeah, it's copycat porn.

291
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,800
We left out this one detail.

292
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,520
The coins. It never hit the papers.

293
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,080
How the hell did this copy-Goat
know about this?

294
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,920
Okay, so you hid it,

295
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
but the medical examiner,
he had to know.

296
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,520
Ed Hayes, yeah, sure.

297
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,080
But he died of cirrhosis.

298
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,800
- That just leaves me.
- And Dix.

299
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,320
Captain, please,
there's no reason...

300
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,600
Go talk to him.

301
00:16:57,680 --> 00:17:00,160
Make sure he didn't tell anyone
about the coins.

302
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,960
Hell, see if he's got any ideas.

303
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:10,080
<i>I'm Lacey White, and this
is the Gotham Seven Goatwatch.</i>

304
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:15,040
<i>Tonight, Gotham's wealthiest
one percent rest fitfully,</i>

305
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:17,760
<i>under a copycat killer's
deadly shadow.</i>

306
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,160
<i>And if you happen to be</i>

307
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,320
<i>one of the city's
high-society silver spoons,</i>

308
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:26,120
<i>then you're probably headed
to the Swiss Alps right now</i>

309
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,320
<i>and away from...</i>

310
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,160
They've got them all running
like rabbits.

311
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,360
Yeah.

312
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,320
I don't know why he chose
an ungulate for his totem,

313
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,520
but he does know how to scare them.

314
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:39,240
You do realize
you happen to be one of them,

315
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,320
don't you, Master Bruce?

316
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,880
Yeah, a firstborn son of Gotham's
rich and powerful.

317
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,640
I don't know, maybe we should leave
town for a little bit.

318
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:50,240
Pop down to the lake house.
You like it there, don't you?

319
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:51,320
I'm not going anywhere.

320
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,560
I have work to do.

321
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:01,160
Besides, why would the Goat take me?

322
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:03,760
There's no one to take me from.

323
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:15,320
- Oh, my God.
- I'm improving your system.

324
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,440
Implementing a rhizomatic
cross index,

325
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:19,200
with your case files classified
by subject,

326
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:22,840
but arranged more like the way
a peat-moss organism grows.

327
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:24,200
You know, laterally.

328
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:28,960
- I had this entire room organized.
- Yes, but now it will be rhizomatic.

329
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,040
Lateral.

330
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,440
What did I ever do to you, Nygma?

331
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,040
What did I do that compels you
to come here

332
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:37,280
with your endless notes suggestions
and riddles?

333
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,440
My God, the riddles.

334
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,720
Are you trying to get me to quit?

335
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:44,240
- You can't want my job.
- No, no, no. I want you.

336
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:51,880
To keep your job and to have it here,
for working.

337
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,720
Okay.

338
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:04,000
I'm getting a sense that
this was somehow inappropriate.

339
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,320
You are so odd.

340
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:15,400
I'll just take my nonhierarchical
data paradigms out of your hair...

341
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:20,720
and leave you to your work.

342
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,840
How long has it been
since you've seen this guy?

343
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,880
Look, Bullock, I know what happened.

344
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,960
- Anybody in your situation...
- Listen.

345
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,480
You think you can shrink my head,
Boy Scout?

346
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,640
Because you can't.

347
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,800
This is the black box, man.

348
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,440
And we don't open the black box,
ever.

349
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,520
Okay, fine.

350
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,880
Why don't you sit your ass down?
I'll be back in a few minutes.

351
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,120
We're both on this case.

352
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,600
- Dix.
- Hey.

353
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,440
What do we have here?

354
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,720
Harvey Bullock, boy detective.

355
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,960
Look at you up there, huh,
living the high life?

356
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:20,800
And me down here,
all broken up with a busted liver.

357
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,720
Don't put that on me, old man.

358
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,600
Your bum liver's between you
and the bottle.

359
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,800
I just busted up your gams
and put you in that chair.

360
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,160
Gotham's golden rule...

361
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:35,280
- No heroes, Bullock.
- No heroes.

362
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:40,520
Listen, Dix, we have to talk
about the case.

363
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,480
About the Goat.

364
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,440
I was wondering when you were going
come and ask for my help.

365
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:48,880
- I'm not asking for your help.
- That don't mean you don't need it.

366
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,920
Who's this? Your partner?

367
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,160
- James Gordon. Nice to meet you.
- Come on, Dix.

368
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,600
Did you ever tell anyone
about Randall Milkie?

369
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,760
The Liberty head pennies?

370
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,840
We said we weren't going to.
We sealed them.

371
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:03,040
I know we sealed them, you jackass.

372
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,560
I told you to seal them.

373
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,960
Okay, but this new killer's
doing the same thing.

374
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:11,320
He's stitching up coins
in the heads of his victims.

375
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,960
Any idea how he came up with that?

376
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,040
I didn't tell anybody.

377
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,640
Ed Hayes didn't tell nobody.

378
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,600
And you didn't tell nobody.

379
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,520
So, what the hell does that mean?

380
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,600
It means we were wrong about Milkie.

381
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,760
- He was not working alone.
- No.

382
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:31,120
You do not have
a copycat killer here.

383
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,880
You do not have a lone killer.

384
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,200
What you have...

385
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,720
is a conspiracy.

386
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,960
A conspiracy to hang rich kids off
local historical landmarks?

387
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:46,080
Yeah, right.

388
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:49,680
He always thinks
he's the smartest one in the room.

389
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,480
I know, right?

390
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,480
That's because I'm always
in a room full of idiots.

391
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,960
Watch out for him.

392
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,760
Oh, yeah? Why's that?

393
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,560
He's a loose cannon.

394
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:07,440
He thinks he's a white knight,
jumping into the breach,

395
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,440
like some idiot in the movies.

396
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,440
We talking about Bullock here?

397
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:14,480
We're talking about Bullock here.

398
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,960
- Harvey Bullock?
- Harvey Bullock.

399
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:20,600
Detective Bullock, do you want
to settle the bill for this month now

400
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,000
or should we send it to you?

401
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,600
You can just put it in the mail,
thanks.

402
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:26,000
Is he getting those magazines
I ordered?

403
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,200
Those are awful magazines, detective.

404
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,840
- But he's getting them?
- Yes, he is.

405
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,600
Good.

406
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,320
Thank you.

407
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,240
No, Mom, I'm just grabbing
a few things. Yes.

408
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,320
Yes, I know.

409
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,120
I'll be at the marina at 9.00.

410
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,200
Okay.

411
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,000
- Here you are.
- Thank you, Anita.

412
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:00,280
Will you put some snack snuff
together, please?

413
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,280
Miss Ember?

414
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:55,600
Anita, have you seen
the tops to my yellow silk...

415
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,800
Anita?

416
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:07,120
Ember Copley was supposed
to meet her parents

417
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,840
tonight at 9.00 at the marina.

418
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:12,960
When she didn't show, they came back,
found the maid out cold, Ember gone.

419
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:15,400
- You think it's our guy?
- It's our guy.

420
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:18,280
He slips in, chloroforms the maid,
grabs Ember.

421
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,560
No sign of B and E,
nothing, like a ghost.

422
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:21,720
Like he had keys.

423
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,000
Randall Milkie had a ritual.

424
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:27,000
Dress the victims, kill them,
do his coin trick.

425
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:28,360
Whole thing took about eight hours.

426
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:30,280
If our copy-Goat's
doing the same thing,

427
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:32,640
we're running out of time.

